<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Wuzilz Blog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/styles.css" />
    <script src="/hamburger.js" defer></script>
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.6.0/jquery.min.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav>
      <div class="nav-left">
        <div class="logo">BlogItOut</div>
      </div>
      <div class="nav-right">
        <div class="menu-toggle">
          <span></span>
          <span></span>
          <span></span>
        </div>
        <ul class="nav-links">
          <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
          <li><a href="#services">Services</a></li>
          <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </nav>
    <div class="Blog-btn">
          <input
              type="button"
              id="createBlogBtn"
              name="createBlogBtn"
              value="Create Blog"
              onclick="createBlog()"
          />
  </div>
    <section>
      <div class="SWE-title">
        <h1>Future SWE??</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="comp-IMG">
        <img src="/images/swe_example.jpeg" />
      </div>
      <div class="SWE-text">
        <p>
          Hello, fellow tech enthusiasts! My journey into the world of software
          engineering began in high school when I discovered the thrill of
          coding. Overcoming challenges in learning data structures and
          algorithms taught me the value of persistence and practice. The
          support from the developer community and resources like Stack Overflow
          and GitHub has been invaluable. Developing a web application using
          HTML, CSS, and JavaScript gave me practical experience and reinforced
          my passion for front-end development. Staying updated with the latest
          technologies, I am currently exploring React.js and Node.js to expand
          my skillset. I aspire to secure an internship where I can work on
          impactful projects and learn from experienced professionals. My
          ultimate goal is to become a full-stack developer, contributing to
          innovative solutions that make a difference in people's lives. The
          path to becoming a software engineer is challenging but immensely
          rewarding, and I am excited about the endless possibilities ahead.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="textBOX">
        <form action="/submit" method="POST">
          <input
            type="text"
            id="textBox"
            name="textBox"
            placeholder="Share you're thoughts!"
            required
          />
          <button type="submit" Submit>Submit</button>
        </form>
      </div>
      <div class="comments-section">
        <h2>Comments</h2>
        <ul>
          <% if (comments.length > 0) { %> <% comments.forEach(comment => { %>
          <li><%= comment %></li>
          <% }); %> <% }else{ %>
          <li style="list-style: none">
            No comments yet. Be the first to share your thoughs!
          </li>
          <% } %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
    <div id="myModal" class="modal">
      <div class="modal-content">
          <span class="close">&times;</span>
          <h1>Create a New Blog</h1>
          <form action="/submit" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
              <label for="title">Title:</label>
              <input type="text" id="title" name="title" required />
              <label for="content">Content:</label>
              <textarea id="content" name="content" required></textarea>
              <label for="image">Image:</label>
              <input type="file" id="image" name="image" accept="image/*" />
              <button type="submit">Submit</button>
          </form>
      </div>
  </div>
  </div>
  </body>
</html>
